1
00:00:02,503 --> 00:00:04,254
My name is Rose Tyler.

2
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:06,757
And this is the story of Torchwood.

3
00:00:07,299 --> 00:00:09,259
The last story I'll ever tell.

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:16,350
Here we are, then. Dad, say hello to Rose.

5
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,518
Hasn't she grown?

6
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:21,355
Welcome to Torchwood.

7
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:23,899
They're Cybermen.

8
00:00:24,942 --> 00:00:26,693
All of the ghosts are Cybermen.

9
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:28,820
MICKEY: That's not Cybermen.
ROSE: Oh, my God!

10
00:00:28,946 --> 00:00:32,449
Exterminate! Exterminate!

11
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:36,286
This is the story of how I died.

12
00:00:39,289 --> 00:00:40,958
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

13
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:17,953
ALL: Exterminate.

14
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:19,580
Daleks!

15
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:23,333
You're called Daleks!

16
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:31,049
I know your name.

17
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:33,260
Think about it, how can I know that?

18
00:01:33,844 --> 00:01:37,014
A human who knows about the Daleks

19
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:39,182
and the Time War.

20
00:01:40,684 --> 00:01:44,062
If you want to know how, then keep us alive.
That's all I'm asking.

21
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:45,439
Me and my friends.

22
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:49,109
-Yeah, Daleks, Time War, me, too.
-Yeah, and me.

23
00:01:50,861 --> 00:01:53,572
You will be necessary.

24
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:57,743
Report! What is the status of the Genesis Ark?

25
00:01:57,868 --> 00:02:00,245
Status, hibernation.

26
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,289
Commence awakening.

27
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:06,835
The Genesis Ark must be protected above all else.

28
00:02:09,421 --> 00:02:11,381
The Daleks? You said they were all dead.

29
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:14,384
Never mind that. What the hell's a "Genesis Ark"?

30
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:15,594
What's down there?

31
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:19,723
She was in that room, with the Sphere.

32
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:22,934
-What's happened to Rose?
-I don't know.

33
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:27,898
I'LL find her.

34
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:31,151
I brought you here.
I'll get you both out, you and your daughter.

35
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:32,611
Jackie, look at me.

36
00:02:32,736 --> 00:02:33,737
Look at me!

37
00:02:35,322 --> 00:02:36,490
I promise you.

38
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:38,909
I give you my word.

39
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:45,207
You will talk to your Central World Authority

40
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,918
and order global surrender.

41
00:02:48,043 --> 00:02:49,419
Oh, do some research.

42
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:52,339
We haven't got a "Central World Authority"”.

43
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:53,924
You have now.

44
00:02:54,049 --> 00:02:57,678
I will speak on all global wavelengths.

45
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:01,807
This broadcast is for humankind.

46
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:07,062
The Cybermen now occupy
every landmass on this planet.

47
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,815
But you need not fear.

48
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,943
Cybermen will remove fear.

49
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:18,281
Cybermen will remove sex and class
and colour and creed.

50
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:21,410
You will become identical.

51
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:24,329
You will become like us.

52
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:28,208
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

53
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,587
SOLDIER: Attack!

54
00:03:50,272 --> 00:03:52,649
I ordered surrender.

55
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,277
They're not taking instructions.

56
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:57,237
Don't you understand?
You're on every street!

57
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,781
You're in their homes!
You've got their children!

58
00:03:59,865 --> 00:04:01,366
Of course they're going to fight!

59
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,910
Which of you is least important?

60
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:05,537
What's that supposed to mean?

61
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,706
Which of you is least important?

62
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:10,208
No. We don't work like that. None of us.

63
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:12,669
Designate the least important.

64
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:15,380
-This is my responsibility.
-No, don't...

65
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:18,258
I, er...

66
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:21,511
I represent the Torchwood Institute.
Anything you need,

67
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:23,138
you come through me.

68
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:24,681
Leave these two alone.

69
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,475
You will kneel.

70
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,977
-What for?
-Kneel!

71
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:37,986
The Daleks need information
about current Earth history.

72
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,405
Yeah, well, I can give you
a certain amount of intelligence,

73
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,365
but nothing that will compromise
homeland security...

74
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,493
Speech is not necessary.

75
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:47,454
We will extract brainwaves.

76
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:54,628
Don't. I'll tell you everything you need.

77
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:55,879
No, don't.

78
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:08,099
Scans detect unknown technology
active within Sphere Chamber.

79
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,186
Cybermen will investigate.

80
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:16,650
Units 10-6-5 and 10-6-6
will investigate Sphere Chamber.

81
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,778
We obey.

82
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:24,908
His mind spoke of
a second species invading Earth.

83
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:28,161
Infected by the superstition of ghosts.

84
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:29,913
You didn't need to kill him!

85
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:33,083
Neither did we need him alive!

86
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:36,503
Dalek Thay, investigate outside.

87
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,255
I obey.

88
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:48,723
Units, open visual link.

89
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,982
Visual contact established.

90
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:59,025
Establish visual contact,

91
00:05:59,109 --> 00:06:01,528
lower communications barrier.

92
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:09,286
(MARCHING)

93
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,877
DALEK: Identify yourselves.

94
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:19,838
CYBERMAN: You will identify first.

95
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:22,424
DALEK: State your identity!

96
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,010
CYBERMAN: You will identify first.

97
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:26,595
DALEK: Identify!

98
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:28,722
It's like Stephen Hawking
meets the speaking clock.

99
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:31,808
...and illogical, you will modify.

100
00:06:31,975 --> 00:06:34,895
Daleks do not take orders.

101
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:38,064
You have identified as Daleks.

102
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:41,484
Outline resembles the inferior species

103
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,612
known as Cybermen.

104
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,698
Rose said about the Daleks,

105
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,533
she was terrified of them.

106
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:51,995
What have they done to her, Doctor? Is she dead?

107
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,163
-(WHISPERING) Phone.
-What?

108
00:06:53,288 --> 00:06:54,581
Phone.

109
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:55,749
(CYBERMEN AND DALEKS ARGUING)

110
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:02,589
(PHONE RINGING)

111
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:06,551
DALEK: ...crude cybernetic constructs
on worldwide scale.

112
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:10,096
She's answered. She's alive.
But why haven't they killed her?

113
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:12,682
-Well, don't complain.
-They must need her for something.

114
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:15,810
We must protect the Genesis Ark.

115
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,228
"Genesis Ark"?

116
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:22,734
Our species are similar,
though your design is inelegant.

117
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:26,571
Daleks have no concept of elegance.

118
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,698
This is obvious.

119
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:32,410
But consider. Our technologies are compatible.

120
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:34,621
Cybermen plus Daleks,

121
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:38,208
together we could upgrade the universe.

122
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:41,211
You propose an alliance?

123
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:43,213
This is correct.

124
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:45,674
Request denied.

125
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:50,220
Hostile elements will be deleted.

126
00:07:52,222 --> 00:07:54,474
DALEK: Exterminate.

127
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:00,814
CYBERMAN: Open visual link.

128
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:03,191
Daleks, be warned.

129
00:08:03,274 --> 00:08:07,237
You have declared war upon the Cybermen.

130
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:11,658
This is not war. This is pest control.

131
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:14,536
We have five million Cybermen.

132
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,496
How many are you?

133
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:18,123
Four.

134
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:22,794
You would destroy the Cybermen with four Daleks?

135
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:26,756
We would destroy the Cybermen with one Dalek.

136
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:31,344
You are superior in only one respect.

137
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:32,929
What is that?

138
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:36,016
You are better at dying.

139
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:39,185
Raise communications barrier.

140
00:08:39,686 --> 00:08:40,812
DALEK: Wait.

141
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:41,938
Lost her.

142
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:44,274
Rewind image by nine rels.

143
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:46,943
Identify grid Seven Gamma Flame.

144
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:51,197
This male registers as enemy.

145
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:55,118
-The female's heartbeat has increased.
-Yeah, tell me about it.

146
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:58,413
-Identify him!
-All right, then.

147
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:00,623
If you really want to know.

148
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:02,917
That's the Doctor.

149
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,464
Five million Cybermen, easy.

150
00:09:08,173 --> 00:09:11,468
One Doctor? Now you're scared.

151
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:17,599
Quarantine the Sphere Chamber.
Start emergency upgrading.

152
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:19,642
Begin with these personnel.

153
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:25,774
No, you can't do this! We've surrendered!
We've surrendered!

154
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,025
Keep this one.

155
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:32,489
His increased adrenaline suggests
that he has vital Dalek information.

156
00:09:32,614 --> 00:09:35,492
-Stop them! I don't want to go! Doctor!
-I demand you leave that woman alone.

157
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,161
-You promised me. You gave me your word.
-I won't help you unless

158
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:39,996
you leave that woman alone.
Jackie, don't fight them...

159
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:45,126
Cyberthreat irrelevant.
Concentrate on the Genesis Ark.

160
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,550
Why are we being kept alive?

161
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:57,013
-They might need me.
-What?

162
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:00,100
What is it?

163
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:04,354
(MAN SCREAMING)

164
00:10:05,188 --> 00:10:06,606
What happens in there?

165
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:09,025
What's upgrading mean? What do they do?

166
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,195
I think they remove the brain.

167
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:16,241
Sorry. I think they remove the brain

168
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,159
and they put it into a suit of arm our.

169
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:21,329
That's what these things are.

170
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:24,374
-They're us.
-Next.

171
00:10:24,874 --> 00:10:28,628
This is your fault. You and your Torchwood!

172
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,380
You've killed us all!

173
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:33,758
I did my duty. For Queen and Country.

174
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:37,387
I did my duty.

175
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:39,639
I did my duty.

176
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,475
Oh, God.

177
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:43,977
I did my duty.

178
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:45,562
(YVONNE SCREAMING)

179
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:52,777
-You are proof.
-Of what?

180
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:56,573
That emotions destroy you.

181
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,449
Yeah, I am.

182
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:03,705
Mind you, I quite like hope.

183
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,249
Hope's a good emotion.

184
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,418
And here it comes.

185
00:11:09,586 --> 00:11:10,670
(SHOUTING ORDERS)

186
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:23,099
Doctor. Good to see you again.

187
00:11:26,853 --> 00:11:27,979
Jake?

188
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:30,773
The Cybermen came through
from one world to another,

189
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,108
and so did we.

190
00:11:34,444 --> 00:11:35,612
No!

191
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:37,655
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

192
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:41,534
Cyberleader One has been terminated.

193
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:44,913
Explain. Download shared files.

194
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:51,294
I will be upgraded to Cyberleader.

195
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:02,972
Defend this room.

196
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:04,724
Chrissie, monitor communications.

197
00:12:04,807 --> 00:12:07,727
Kill one Cyberleader
and they just download into another.

198
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:09,145
Move!

199
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:15,443
You can't just hop from one world to another.
You can't.

200
00:12:15,944 --> 00:12:18,780
We just did. With these.

201
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,451
But that's impossible.
You can't have this sort of technology.

202
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:26,371
We've got our own version of Torchwood.
They developed it.

203
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:28,873
Do you wanna come and see?

204
00:12:29,999 --> 00:12:31,251
No!

205
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:38,549
Parallel Earth,

206
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:40,134
parallel Torchwood.

207
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,221
Except we found out what the Institute was doing,

208
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:45,265
and the People's Republic took control.

209
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:47,767
I've got to get back.
Rose is in danger, and her mother.

210
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:49,227
That would be Jackie.

211
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:52,772
My wife in a parallel universe.

212
00:12:53,648 --> 00:12:56,442
And as for you, Doctor.
At least this time, I know who you are.

213
00:12:56,818 --> 00:12:59,779
Right, yes, fine, hooray,
but I've got to get back, right now.

214
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:01,572
No, you're not in charge here.

215
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:06,035
This is our world, not yours.
And you're going to listen for once.

216
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:12,625
I could transport out of here,
but it only carries one.

217
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:13,793
And I'm not leaving you.

218
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:15,712
Follow me anywhere.

219
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,797
What did I do to you all those years ago?

220
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:19,382
Guess I'm just stupid.

221
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,386
You're the bravest man I've ever met.

222
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:26,014
-What about the Doctor?
-Oh, all right.

223
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:28,558
Bravest human.

224
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:31,185
Well, I can't think what the Daleks need with me.

225
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:33,396
I'm nothing to them.

226
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:34,939
You could be.

227
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:40,028
Whatever's inside that Ark, it's waking up.
And I've seen this happen before.

228
00:13:40,111 --> 00:13:43,072
First time I saw a Dalek, it was broken.

229
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:46,743
It was dying. But I touched it.

230
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:49,454
And the moment I did that

231
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:50,621
I brought it back to life.

232
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,585
So the Doctor said,

233
00:13:56,461 --> 00:13:59,756
when you travel in time, in the Tardis,
you soak up all this...

234
00:14:00,882 --> 00:14:02,550
background radiation.

235
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:05,094
It's harmless, it's just there.

236
00:14:07,138 --> 00:14:08,765
But in the Time War,

237
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:11,601
the Daleks evolved so they could use it
as a power supply.

238
00:14:12,185 --> 00:14:14,520
-I love it when you talk technical.
-Shut up.

239
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:20,360
But if the Daleks have got something
inside that thing and it needs waking up...

240
00:14:20,443 --> 00:14:21,611
They need you.

241
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,947
You've travelled in time.
Either one of us would do.

242
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:27,492
But why would they build something
they can't open themselves?

243
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:30,411
The technology is stolen.

244
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:34,791
The Ark is not of Dalek design.

245
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:36,334
Then who built it?

246
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:38,378
The Time Lords.

247
00:14:38,461 --> 00:14:41,923
This is all that survives of their home world.

248
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:46,135
-But what's inside?
-The future.

249
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:53,935
When you left this world,
you warned us there'd be more Cybermen.

250
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,187
So we sealed them inside the factories.

251
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,106
Except people argued.

252
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:00,900
Said they were living,

253
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,528
we should help them.

254
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:05,405
And the debate went on,

255
00:15:05,488 --> 00:15:08,032
but all that time, the Cybermen made plans.

256
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:10,535
Infiltrated this version of Torchwood.

257
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:13,913
Mapped themselves onto your world
and then vanished.

258
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:15,998
-When was this?
-Three years ago.

259
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:21,546
It's taken them three years to cross the Void,

260
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:23,172
but we can pop to and fro in a second?

261
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:26,843
Must be the sheer mass of five million
Cybermen crossing all at once.

262
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:29,178
Yeah. Mickey said you'd rattle off
that sort of stuff.

263
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:30,847
Where is the Mickey boy?

264
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,140
He went ahead first.

265
00:15:32,974 --> 00:15:35,685
Any chance to go and find Miss Rose Tyler.

266
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,563
She's your daughter.

267
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,524
-You do know that? Did Mickey explain?
-She's not mine.

268
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:44,277
She's the child of a dead man.

269
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:47,905
Look at it. A world at peace.

270
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:52,285
-We're calling this the Golden Age.
-Who's the president now?

271
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:56,414
-A woman called Harriet Jones.
-I'd keep an eye on her.

272
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:58,207
But it's a lie.

273
00:15:58,332 --> 00:16:01,461
Temperatures have risen by two degrees
in the past six months.

274
00:16:01,544 --> 00:16:04,714
The ice caps are melting.
They're saying all of this is gonna be flooded.

275
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:08,384
That's not just global warming, is it?

276
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:11,220
-No.
-It's the breach.

277
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:15,475
I've been trying to tell you.
Travel between parallel worlds is impossible.

278
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:18,102
Then the Daleks break down
the walls with the Sphere.

279
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:20,146
-"Daleks"?
-Then the Cybermen travelled across,

280
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:22,648
then you lot, those discs, every time you jump

281
00:16:22,732 --> 00:16:25,485
from one reality to another,
you rip a hole in the universe.

282
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:27,570
This planet is starting to boil!

283
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,072
Keep going and both worlds will fall
into the Void.

284
00:16:30,323 --> 00:16:31,991
But you can stop it?

285
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:34,160
The famous Doctor.

286
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:35,661
You can seal the breach.

287
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:38,080
Leaving five million Cybermen
stranded on my Earth.

288
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:40,875
That's your problem.
I'm protecting this world and this world only.

289
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:44,253
Pete Tyler.

290
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:46,422
I knew you when you were dead.

291
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:49,592
Now here you are, fighting the fight.

292
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,094
Alone.

293
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:54,931
There is a chance.

294
00:16:56,098 --> 00:16:57,600
Back on my world,

295
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:00,019
Jackie Tyler might still be alive.

296
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,688
-My wife died.
-Her husband died. Good match.

297
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:04,857
There's more important things at stake.

298
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:07,777
Doctor.

299
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:09,946
Help us.

300
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,615
What? Close the breach?

301
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:15,284
Stop the Cybermen? Defeat the Daleks?

302
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:17,286
Do you believe I can do that?

303
00:17:18,955 --> 00:17:19,956
Yes.

304
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:22,833
Maybe, that's all I need.

305
00:17:24,335 --> 00:17:25,461
Off we go, then.

306
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:30,800
First of all, I need to make a phone call.
You don't mind?

307
00:17:30,925 --> 00:17:31,968
You two, guard the door.

308
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,888
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

309
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:38,099
-Oh, my God, help me.
-Jackie, you're alive.

310
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:41,811
-They tried to download me but I ran away.
-Listen, tell me, where are you?

311
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:44,480
I don't know. Staircase.

312
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:47,567
Yeah, which one?
Is there any sort of sign, anything to identify it?

313
00:17:47,650 --> 00:17:50,778
-Yes, a fire extinguisher.
-Yeah, that helps.

314
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:53,573
Oh, wait a minute. It says N3.

315
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:56,284
North corner, staircase three.
Just keep low, we're trying our best.

316
00:17:56,409 --> 00:17:58,786
-Oh, don't leave me.
-I've got to go. I'm sorry.

317
00:18:00,288 --> 00:18:03,416
-Jacqueline Andrea Suzette Tyler.
-She's not my wife.

318
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:06,085
I was at the wedding. You got her name wrong.

319
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,421
Now, Jakey-boy.
If I could open the bonding chamber on this thing,

320
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:09,755
it could work on polycarbide.

321
00:18:09,839 --> 00:18:12,508
-What's "polycarbide”?
-The skin of a Dalek.

322
00:18:16,679 --> 00:18:18,764
Sorry. No white flag,

323
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:20,850
only had a sheet of A4. Same difference.

324
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:23,561
Do you surrender?

325
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:26,230
I surrender, unto you...

326
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,358
a very good idea.

327
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:33,654
Final stage of awakening!

328
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:37,366
Your handprint will open the Ark.

329
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,826
Well tough, 'cause I'm not doing it.

330
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:41,871
Obey or the male will die.

331
00:18:41,996 --> 00:18:43,706
-I can't let them...
-Rose, don't!

332
00:18:43,873 --> 00:18:47,043
-Place your hand upon the casket.
-All right!

333
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:50,379
But you're gonna kill us anyway, so what the hell.

334
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:54,050
If you, erm...

335
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:58,012
escaped the Time War,
don't you want to know what happened?

336
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:00,723
-Place your hand...
-What happened to the Emperor?

337
00:19:01,057 --> 00:19:03,601
The Emperor survived?

338
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:05,686
Until he met me.

339
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:09,565
'Cause if these are gonna be my last words,
then you're gonna listen.

340
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,234
I met the Emperor.

341
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:16,072
And I took the Time Vortex
and poured it into his head

342
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,907
and turned him into dust.

343
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:20,284
Did you get that?

344
00:19:21,452 --> 00:19:22,662
The God of all Daleks

345
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:24,413
and I destroyed him.

346
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:28,584
You will be exterminated!

347
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:30,836
Oh, now, hold on, wait a minute...

348
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:34,256
Alert. Alert. You are the Doctor.

349
00:19:34,382 --> 00:19:37,426
Sensors report he is unarmed.

350
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:38,886
That's me. Always.

351
00:19:38,969 --> 00:19:41,347
Then you are powerless.

352
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:43,224
Not me. Never.

353
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:46,352
-How are you?
-Oh. Same old, you know.

354
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:49,605
Good. And Micketty-Mick-Mickey, nice to see you.

355
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:50,690
And you, boss.

356
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:53,275
Social interaction will cease.

357
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,862
How did you survive the Time War?

358
00:19:57,071 --> 00:19:59,990
By fighting. On the front line.

359
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:02,493
I was there at the Fall of Arcadia.

360
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:05,621
Some day, I might even come to terms with that.

361
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,791
But you lot ran away.

362
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:11,836
We had to survive.

363
00:20:11,961 --> 00:20:14,046
The last four Daleks in existence.

364
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:17,174
-So what's so special about you?
-Doctor, they've got names.

365
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:20,553
I mean, Daleks don't have names, do they?
But one of them said...

366
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:24,223
-I am Dalek Thay.
-Dalek Sec.

367
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:27,560
-Dalek Jast.
-Dalek Caan.

368
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:30,980
So that's it. At last.

369
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:33,941
The Cult of Skaro.
I thought you were just a legend.

370
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:36,527
-Who are they?
-A secret order,

371
00:20:37,153 --> 00:20:39,905
above and beyond the Emperor himself.

372
00:20:40,531 --> 00:20:42,783
Their job was to imagine.

373
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,910
Think as the enemy thinks.

374
00:20:44,994 --> 00:20:46,954
Even dare to have names,

375
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:49,582
all to find new ways of killing.

376
00:20:50,124 --> 00:20:52,835
But that thing, they said it was yours.
I mean Time Lords, they built it,

377
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,295
what does it do?

378
00:20:54,378 --> 00:20:55,880
I don't know. Never seen it before.

379
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:58,340
But it's Time Lord.

380
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:02,178
Both sides had secrets.
What is it, what have you done?

381
00:21:02,303 --> 00:21:06,515
Time Lord science will restore Dalek supremacy.

382
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:10,269
What does that mean? What sort
of "Time Lord science"? What do you mean?

383
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:12,855
They said one touch from a time traveller
will wake it up.

384
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:15,858
Technology using the one thing a Dalek can't do.

385
00:21:16,859 --> 00:21:18,110
Touch.

386
00:21:18,861 --> 00:21:22,865
Sealed inside your casing,
not feeling anything, ever.

387
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:28,537
From birth to death,
locked inside a cold metal cage,

388
00:21:28,871 --> 00:21:30,122
completely alone.

389
00:21:31,874 --> 00:21:34,043
That explains your voice.

390
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:36,796
No wonder you scream.

391
00:21:37,046 --> 00:21:39,507
The Doctor will open the Ark!

392
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:41,133
(CHUCKLING)

393
00:21:41,592 --> 00:21:42,968
The Doctor will not.

394
00:21:43,052 --> 00:21:45,930
You have no way of resisting.

395
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:49,517
Well, you got me there. Although...

396
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:51,727
there is always this.

397
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:54,146
A sonic probe?

398
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:57,525
-That's screwdriver.
-It is harmless.

399
00:21:57,608 --> 00:22:01,070
Oh, yes. Harmless is just the word.
That's why I like it.

400
00:22:01,237 --> 00:22:04,865
Doesn't kill, doesn't wound, doesn't maim,
but I'll tell you what it does do.

401
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,952
It is very good at opening doors.

402
00:22:13,499 --> 00:22:15,417
QYBERMAN: Terminate. Terminate.

403
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:20,047
Alert. Casing impaired, casing impaired.

404
00:22:20,172 --> 00:22:21,632
Rose, get out.

405
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:25,636
DALEK: Firepower insufficient,
firepower insufficient.

406
00:22:27,096 --> 00:22:28,138
Come on.

407
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:32,184
CYBERMAN: Daleks will be deleted. Delete, delete.

408
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:34,728
Mickey, come on.

409
00:22:34,854 --> 00:22:36,772
DALEK: Adapt to weaponry.

410
00:22:37,398 --> 00:22:39,775
Firepower restored.

411
00:22:46,657 --> 00:22:49,618
Cybermen, primary target.

412
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:54,748
Jake, protect the stairwell.
The rest of you, come on.

413
00:22:59,295 --> 00:23:03,299
Cybermen have been exterminated.
Daleks are supreme.

414
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:06,385
The Genesis Ark is primed.

415
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:11,807
The Ark needs area of thirty square miles.

416
00:23:11,891 --> 00:23:13,309
Move.

417
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:18,772
Genesis Ark mobile.

418
00:23:22,151 --> 00:23:23,527
I just fell, I didn't mean it.

419
00:23:23,611 --> 00:23:25,154
Mickey, without us, they'd have opened it by force,

420
00:23:25,279 --> 00:23:27,948
and to do that, they'd have blown up
the sun, so you've done us a favour.

421
00:23:28,032 --> 00:23:29,241
Now, run.

422
00:23:45,341 --> 00:23:48,010
-You will be upgraded.
-No, but you can't...

423
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:03,734
Pete?

424
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:06,612
Hello, Jacks.

425
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:10,199
I said there were ghosts. But that's not fair.
Why him?

426
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,744
-I'm not a ghost.
-But you're dead.

427
00:24:14,203 --> 00:24:16,914
You died 20 years ago, Pete.

428
00:24:17,039 --> 00:24:20,042
It's Pete from a different universe.

429
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:22,544
There are parallel worlds, Jackie.

430
00:24:22,628 --> 00:24:25,631
Every single decision we make
creates a parallel existence,

431
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:28,008
-a different dimension where...
-Oh, you can shut up.

432
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:37,267
-You look old.
-You don't.

433
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:42,731
How can you be standing there?

434
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:44,650
Just got lucky.

435
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:46,110
Lived my life.

436
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:50,406
But you were left on your own.

437
00:24:51,949 --> 00:24:56,078
-You didn't marry again or...?
-There was never anyone else.

438
00:24:58,288 --> 00:25:02,084
Twenty years, though. Look at me.
I never left that flat.

439
00:25:03,085 --> 00:25:06,839
-Did nothing with myself.
-You brought her up.

440
00:25:07,423 --> 00:25:08,841
Rose Tyler.

441
00:25:10,134 --> 00:25:11,760
That's not bad.

442
00:25:13,137 --> 00:25:14,179
Yeah.

443
00:25:14,722 --> 00:25:17,433
In my world, it worked.

444
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:22,604
All those daft little plans of mine, it worked.

445
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,483
-Made me rich.
-I don't care about that.

446
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:30,195
-How rich?
-Very.

447
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,115
I don't care about that.

448
00:25:34,616 --> 00:25:36,243
How very?

449
00:25:44,126 --> 00:25:45,878
Thing is though, Jacks,

450
00:25:46,795 --> 00:25:47,880
you're not my wife.

451
00:25:49,506 --> 00:25:53,343
I'm sorry, but you're not. I mean we both...

452
00:25:57,765 --> 00:25:59,683
You know, it's just sort of...

453
00:26:02,186 --> 00:26:03,353
Oh, come here.

454
00:26:15,157 --> 00:26:18,077
-Exterminate.
-Delete.

455
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:21,455
-Exterminate.
-Delete, delete.

456
00:26:23,582 --> 00:26:27,336
-Exterminate.
-Delete, delete.

457
00:26:31,215 --> 00:26:33,217
Exterminate.

458
00:26:37,304 --> 00:26:38,680
Exterminate.

459
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,895
Delete.

460
00:26:47,856 --> 00:26:49,566
(MEN SHOUTING)

461
00:26:50,484 --> 00:26:54,571
Emergency, all units will converge
on the Torchwood Tower.

462
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:58,450
Repeat, all Cybermen to Torchwood.

463
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:37,489
Come on, please.

464
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:55,591
Override roof mechanism.

465
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:00,137
Elevate.

466
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:06,977
What are they doing?
Why do they need to get outside?

467
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:11,607
Time Lord science.
What Time Lord science, what is it?

468
00:28:16,862 --> 00:28:18,655
We've got to see what it's doing,
we've got to go back up.

469
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:20,407
Come on, all of you. Top floor!

470
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:24,077
That's 45 floors up.
Believe me, I've done them all.

471
00:28:25,412 --> 00:28:26,955
We could always take the Lift.

472
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:37,633
The Genesis Ark will open.

473
00:28:53,941 --> 00:28:55,567
Time Lord science.

474
00:28:56,235 --> 00:28:58,403
It's bigger on the inside.

475
00:28:58,946 --> 00:29:01,156
The Time Lords put those Daleks in there?

476
00:29:01,782 --> 00:29:03,242
What for?

477
00:29:03,825 --> 00:29:05,494
It's a prison ship.

478
00:29:06,703 --> 00:29:07,746
How many Daleks?

479
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:10,040
Millions.

480
00:29:37,484 --> 00:29:42,155
Exterminate all life forms below. Exterminate.

481
00:29:44,574 --> 00:29:45,617
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

482
00:29:48,996 --> 00:29:51,581
I'm sorry, but you've had it.
This world's going to crash and burn.

483
00:29:51,707 --> 00:29:52,833
There's nothing we can do.

484
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:54,918
We're going home. Jacks, take this.

485
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:58,046
-You're coming with us.
-But they're destroying the city.

486
00:29:58,297 --> 00:30:02,050
Oh, I'd forgotten you could argue.
It's not just London. It's the whole world.

487
00:30:02,175 --> 00:30:06,138
But there's another world,
just waiting for you, Jacks, and it's safe.

488
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:08,307
As long as the Doctor closes the breach.

489
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:10,225
Doctor?

490
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:14,229
Oh, I'm ready.

491
00:30:14,563 --> 00:30:16,648
I've got the equipment right here,
thank you, Torchwood.

492
00:30:16,732 --> 00:30:18,900
Slam it down and close off both universes.

493
00:30:18,984 --> 00:30:22,195
But we can't just leave. What about the Daleks?
And the Cybermen?

494
00:30:22,279 --> 00:30:26,366
They're part of the problem and that
makes them part of the solution. Oh, yes.

495
00:30:27,242 --> 00:30:30,495
Well? Isn't anyone going to ask?
What is it with the glasses?

496
00:30:30,579 --> 00:30:33,081
-What is it with the glasses?
-I can see. That's what.

497
00:30:33,332 --> 00:30:36,209
'Cause we've got two separate worlds,
but in between the two separate worlds,

498
00:30:36,293 --> 00:30:38,420
we've got the Void,
that's where the Daleks were hiding,

499
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:40,464
and the Cybermen travelled
through the Void to get here

500
00:30:40,589 --> 00:30:42,758
and you lot, one world to another, via the Void.

501
00:30:42,924 --> 00:30:45,677
I like that, "via the Void". Look.

502
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:48,055
I've been through it, do you see?

503
00:30:48,138 --> 00:30:50,098
COMPUTER: Reboot in three minutes.

504
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:52,726
-What is it?
-Void stuff.

505
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:56,605
-Like background radiation.
-That's it.

506
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:58,398
Look at the others.

507
00:30:58,482 --> 00:31:01,610
And the only one who hasn't been
through the Void, your mother.

508
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:05,072
-First time she's looked normal in her life.
-0i.

509
00:31:05,155 --> 00:31:07,824
But the Daleks lived inside the Void.
They're bristling with it.

510
00:31:07,908 --> 00:31:11,495
Cybermen, all of them, I just open the Void.
And reverse.

511
00:31:11,703 --> 00:31:13,955
The Void stuff gets sucked back inside.

512
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:16,708
-Pulling them all in.
-Pulling them all in.

513
00:31:16,792 --> 00:31:19,795
-Sorry, but what's the Void?
-The dead space.

514
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:21,505
Some people call it hell.

515
00:31:21,588 --> 00:31:24,925
So you're sending the Daleks
and the Cybermen to hell?

516
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:29,012
Man, I told you he was good.

517
00:31:29,096 --> 00:31:32,474
But it's like you said. We've all got Void stuff.

518
00:31:33,058 --> 00:31:35,602
Me, too, 'cause we went to that parallel world.

519
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:42,067
We're all contaminated. We'll get pulled in.

520
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:43,485
That's why you've got to go.

521
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:45,612
COMPUTER: Reboot in two minutes.

522
00:31:46,029 --> 00:31:49,991
Back to Pete's world.
Hey, we should call it that. "Pete's World".

523
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:54,246
I'm opening the Void, but only on this side.

524
00:31:56,123 --> 00:31:58,208
You'll be safe on that side.

525
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:01,378
And then you close it? For good?

526
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:04,840
The breach itself is soaked in Void stuff.
In the end, it'll close itself.

527
00:32:05,173 --> 00:32:07,092
And that's it. Kaput.

528
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:11,596
-But you stay on this side?
-But you'll get pulled in.

529
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:18,728
That's why I got these.

530
00:32:19,688 --> 00:32:21,982
I'll just have to hold on tight.
Been doing it all my life.

531
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:24,151
-I'm supposed to go?
-Yeah.

532
00:32:24,234 --> 00:32:27,195
To another world? And then it gets sealed off?

533
00:32:27,279 --> 00:32:28,321
Yeah.

534
00:32:30,198 --> 00:32:31,241
Forever?

535
00:32:32,868 --> 00:32:34,619
(SCOFFING) That's not gonna happen.

536
00:32:35,871 --> 00:32:38,248
We haven't got time to argue.
The plan works. We're going.

537
00:32:38,331 --> 00:32:40,375
-You, too, all of us.
-I'm not leaving him.

538
00:32:40,459 --> 00:32:42,461
-I'm not going without her.
-Oh, my God, we're going.

539
00:32:42,544 --> 00:32:44,838
I've had 20 years without you, so button it.

540
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:46,131
I'm not leaving her!

541
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:48,258
-But you've got to.
-Well, that's tough.

542
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:49,593
Mum.

543
00:32:49,676 --> 00:32:51,553
COMPUTER: Reboot in one minute.

544
00:32:51,678 --> 00:32:54,848
I had a life with you for 19 years.

545
00:32:56,766 --> 00:32:58,393
But then I met the Doctor.

546
00:32:59,478 --> 00:33:02,522
And all the things I've seen him do for me,

547
00:33:03,648 --> 00:33:05,734
for you, for all of us,

548
00:33:06,902 --> 00:33:10,280
for the whole stupid planet

549
00:33:10,405 --> 00:33:13,617
and every planet out there. He does it alone, Mum.

550
00:33:16,786 --> 00:33:18,538
But not anymore.

551
00:33:20,874 --> 00:33:22,709
'Cause now he's got me.

552
00:33:32,636 --> 00:33:33,678
Oh, no, you don't.

553
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:36,264
He's not doing that to me again.

554
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:42,437
I think this is the on switch.

555
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:45,398
But I've got to go back.

556
00:33:45,482 --> 00:33:48,276
The Doctor said, every time we use
one of these, it damages the whole world.

557
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:49,945
-Now that's it.
-She's your daughter.

558
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:52,781
She's your daughter, not mine. That's an order.

559
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:56,535
Mickey, tell him. Tell him, Mickey! Mickey!

560
00:33:56,785 --> 00:34:00,413
Once the breach collapses, that's it.
You'll never be able to see her again.

561
00:34:00,497 --> 00:34:01,581
Your own mother!

562
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:05,210
I made my choice a long time ago.
And I'm never going to leave you.

563
00:34:07,629 --> 00:34:09,047
So, what can I do to help?

564
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:12,717
COMPUTER: Systems rebooted. Open access.

565
00:34:12,801 --> 00:34:17,055
Those coordinates over there, set them all at six.
And hurry up.

566
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:25,981
Get away from me.

567
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:29,985
We've got Cybermen on the way up.

568
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:34,114
-How many floors down?
-Just one.

569
00:34:35,824 --> 00:34:38,159
We will retreat through the breach.

570
00:34:38,285 --> 00:34:40,662
Regain the home world.

571
00:34:43,832 --> 00:34:45,584
FEMALE VOICE: You will not pass.

572
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:47,752
What is the meaning of this?

573
00:34:47,836 --> 00:34:49,879
You will not pass.

574
00:34:50,547 --> 00:34:51,590
(CYBERMEN SHOUTING)

575
00:34:53,133 --> 00:34:56,094
I did my duty. For Queen and Country.

576
00:34:56,177 --> 00:34:59,180
I did my duty. For Queen and Country.

577
00:34:59,264 --> 00:35:02,726
I did my duty. For Queen and Country.

578
00:35:04,352 --> 00:35:05,937
COMPUTER: Levers operational.

579
00:35:06,021 --> 00:35:07,897
That's more like it. Bit of a smile.

580
00:35:08,023 --> 00:35:09,774
-The old team.
-Hope and Glory.

581
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:11,109
Mutt and Jeff. Shiver and Shake.

582
00:35:11,276 --> 00:35:13,194
-Which one's Shiver?
-Oh, I'm Shake.

583
00:35:18,575 --> 00:35:19,618
Press the red button.

584
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:24,873
Breach active. It is the Doctor. Exterminate him.

585
00:35:25,749 --> 00:35:27,208
Exterminate!

586
00:35:27,876 --> 00:35:29,961
When it starts, just hold on tight.
Shouldn't be too bad for us,

587
00:35:30,045 --> 00:35:33,214
but the Daleks and the Cybermen
are steeped in Void stuff. Are you ready?

588
00:35:33,506 --> 00:35:34,966
So are they.

589
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:38,094
Let's do it.

590
00:35:41,014 --> 00:35:42,057
COMPUTER: Online.

591
00:35:46,645 --> 00:35:47,687
(DALEKS SCREAMING)

592
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:56,279
The breach is open. Into the Void!

593
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:07,624
(CYBERMEN AND DALEKS SHOUTING)

594
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:20,428
Emergency temporal shift.

595
00:36:44,369 --> 00:36:45,453
COMPUTER: Offline.

596
00:36:48,123 --> 00:36:49,124
Hold on!

597
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:02,846
I've got to get it upright.

598
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:19,279
COMPUTER: Online and locked.

599
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:23,575
Rose. Hold on!

600
00:37:28,705 --> 00:37:29,748
Hold on!

601
00:37:44,387 --> 00:37:46,431
No!

602
00:38:13,875 --> 00:38:15,460
COMPUTER: Systems closed.

603
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:20,048
Take me back. Take me back.

604
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:23,218
Take me back.

605
00:38:28,515 --> 00:38:29,557
It's stopped working.

606
00:38:31,851 --> 00:38:32,894
He did it.

607
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:36,439
He closed the breach.

608
00:40:19,834 --> 00:40:21,502
DOCTOR: Rose.

609
00:40:26,090 --> 00:40:27,842
ROSE: Last night I had a dream.

610
00:40:27,926 --> 00:40:29,052
DOCTOR: Rose.

611
00:40:29,135 --> 00:40:32,347
ROSE: I heard a voice. And it was calling my name.

612
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:34,057
DOCTOR: Rose.

613
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:37,060
Rose.

614
00:40:38,895 --> 00:40:39,979
Rose.

615
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:43,441
I had a dream.

616
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:45,568
I told Mum and Dad and Mickey.

617
00:40:46,527 --> 00:40:50,073
Anyone else would think I was mad,
but not those three.

618
00:40:50,531 --> 00:40:51,699
They believed it.

619
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:56,037
Because they've met the Doctor.
So they listened to the dream.

620
00:40:56,371 --> 00:40:58,873
He was calling me, and...

621
00:41:04,212 --> 00:41:06,381
And that night, we packed up.

622
00:41:13,388 --> 00:41:15,682
Got into Dad's old Jeep. And off we went.

623
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:26,192
Just like the dream said.

624
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:29,821
We followed the voice.

625
00:41:31,197 --> 00:41:32,573
Crossed the water,

626
00:41:34,575 --> 00:41:37,620
kept on driving, hundreds and hundreds of mile.

627
00:41:40,832 --> 00:41:42,750
Because he's calling.

628
00:41:42,875 --> 00:41:43,918
DOCTOR: Rose.

629
00:41:46,004 --> 00:41:47,797
Here I am, at last.

630
00:41:49,215 --> 00:41:51,342
And this is the story of how I died.

631
00:42:07,608 --> 00:42:10,111
-Where are you?
-Inside the Tardis.

632
00:42:10,653 --> 00:42:13,322
There's one tiny little gap in the universe left.

633
00:42:13,448 --> 00:42:14,615
Just about to close.

634
00:42:16,284 --> 00:42:18,119
And it takes a lot of power to send this projection.

635
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:20,997
I'm in orbit around a supernova.

636
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:23,624
I'm burning up a sun just to say goodbye.

637
00:42:27,628 --> 00:42:30,506
-You look like a ghost.
-Hold on.

638
00:42:41,976 --> 00:42:45,646
-Can1...7
-I'm still just an image. No touch.

639
00:42:48,149 --> 00:42:52,445
-Can't you come through properly?
-The whole thing would fracture.

640
00:42:52,528 --> 00:42:56,032
-Two universes would collapse.
-So?

641
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:04,248
Where are we? Where did the gap come out?

642
00:43:04,332 --> 00:43:07,585
-We're in Norway.
-Norway. Right.

643
00:43:07,668 --> 00:43:09,879
About 50 miles out of Bergen,

644
00:43:10,588 --> 00:43:15,176
-it's called Darlig Ulv Stranden.
-Dalek?

645
00:43:15,426 --> 00:43:18,679
Darlig. It's Norwegian for bad.

646
00:43:20,848 --> 00:43:24,018
This translates as Bad Wolf Bay.

647
00:43:29,857 --> 00:43:31,192
How long have we got?

648
00:43:32,193 --> 00:43:35,196
About two minutes.

649
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:39,534
I can't think of what to say.

650
00:43:45,581 --> 00:43:47,542
You've still got Mr Mickey, then.

651
00:43:48,543 --> 00:43:50,211
There's five of us now.

652
00:43:50,837 --> 00:43:54,382
Mum, Dad, Mickey and the baby.

653
00:43:55,633 --> 00:43:56,676
You're not...

654
00:43:58,594 --> 00:44:00,888
No. It's Mum.

655
00:44:02,223 --> 00:44:05,184
She's three months gone. More Tylers on the way.

656
00:44:07,395 --> 00:44:11,649
-And what about you, what are you...
-Yeah, I'm back working in the shop.

657
00:44:13,568 --> 00:44:16,737
-Well, good for you.
-Shut up.

658
00:44:16,821 --> 00:44:17,864
Nah, I'm not.

659
00:44:19,115 --> 00:44:22,076
There's still a Torchwood on this planet.
It's open for business.

660
00:44:23,953 --> 00:44:26,706
I think I know a thing or two about aliens.

661
00:44:26,789 --> 00:44:29,417
Rose Tyler. Defender of the Earth.

662
00:44:33,504 --> 00:44:36,424
You're dead, officially. Back home.

663
00:44:38,467 --> 00:44:41,053
So many people died that day
and you've gone missing.

664
00:44:42,054 --> 00:44:44,432
You're on a list of the dead.

665
00:44:47,101 --> 00:44:48,936
But here you are,

666
00:44:49,353 --> 00:44:51,022
living a life, day after day.

667
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:56,527
The one adventure I can never have.

668
00:44:59,697 --> 00:45:02,283
Am I ever going to see you again?

669
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:07,413
You can't.

670
00:45:08,122 --> 00:45:10,082
What are you going to do?

671
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:12,627
I've got the Tardis.

672
00:45:13,461 --> 00:45:15,796
Same old life. Last of the Time Lords.

673
00:45:17,506 --> 00:45:19,383
On your own?

674
00:45:26,140 --> 00:45:27,141
I._..

675
00:45:34,273 --> 00:45:35,942
I love you.

676
00:45:38,527 --> 00:45:39,570
Quite right, too.

677
00:45:44,909 --> 00:45:46,702
And I suppose...

678
00:45:49,205 --> 00:45:51,040
if it's my last chance to say it,

679
00:45:56,587 --> 00:45:58,589
Rose Tyler...

680
00:47:16,834 --> 00:47:17,877
What?

681
00:47:19,420 --> 00:47:20,463
(EXCLAIMING)

682
00:47:20,588 --> 00:47:22,465
-What?
-Who are you?

683
00:47:24,133 --> 00:47:26,218
-Where am I?
-What?

684
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:29,847
-What the hell is this place?
-What?

